tables.description: The action_tracker table represents a record of actions taken in response to incidents. It stores information about the action, the owner responsible, and the status of the action. This table is typically used in analytics and business workflows to track progress and identify areas for improvement in incident management.

columns.description: The action_id column represents a unique identifier for each action recorded in the action_tracker table. It is an integer value that is used to link actions to incidents and track progress. This column is essential for tracking and analyzing incident management data.

The incident_id column represents the unique identifier for the incident associated with each action recorded in the action_tracker table. It is an integer value that links actions to incidents and enables tracking of incident management progress. This column is critical for incident analysis and risk management.

The action_item column stores a brief description of the action taken in response to an incident. It is a text value that provides context for the action and enables tracking of incident management progress. This column is essential for understanding incident management strategies and identifying areas for improvement.

columns.description: The owner column represents the individual responsible for each action recorded in the action_tracker table. It is a character varying value that stores the name or ID of the owner. This column is critical for tracking accountability and ensuring that actions are completed in a timely manner.

The due_date column represents the deadline for completing each action recorded in the action_tracker table. It is a date value that enables tracking of action completion and identifies potential delays. This column is essential for ensuring that actions are completed on time and that incident management progress is tracked.

The action_status column represents the current status of each action recorded in the action_tracker table. It is a character varying value that stores the status (e.g., 'in progress', 'completed', 'deferred'). This column is critical for tracking action completion and identifying areas for improvement in incident management.

tables.description: The employees table stores information about the company's workforce, including employee IDs, full names, departments, job titles, and email addresses. This table is crucial for HR management and is often used to track employee data, generate reports, and analyze workforce demographics.

columns.description: The employee_id column represents a unique identifier for each employee in the employees table. It is an integer value that is used to link employees to their records and track workforce data. This column is essential for HR management and workforce analysis.

The full_name column stores the full name of each employee in the employees table. It is a character varying value that provides context for employee records and enables tracking of workforce demographics. This column is critical for HR management and employee communication.

The department column represents the department or team that each employee belongs to in the employees table. It is a character varying value that stores the department name or ID. This column is essential for tracking workforce structure and identifying areas for improvement in team management.

The job_title column represents the job title or role of each employee in the employees table. It is a character varying value that provides context for employee records and enables tracking of workforce demographics. This column is critical for HR management and employee development.

The email column stores the email address of each employee in the employees table. It is a character varying value that enables communication with employees and tracks workforce contact information. This column is essential for HR management and employee communication.

tables.description: The incidents table represents a record of all incidents that have occurred, including the incident date, category, site location, severity, and description. This table is used to track and analyze incident data, identify trends, and inform risk management strategies.

columns.description: The incident_id column represents a unique identifier for each incident recorded in the incidents table. It is an integer value that is used to link incidents to their records and track incident data. This column is critical for incident analysis and risk management.

The incident_date column represents the date on which each incident occurred in the incidents table. It is a date value that enables tracking of incident frequency and identifies trends. This column is essential for incident analysis and risk management.

The incident_category column represents the category or type of each incident recorded in the incidents table. It is a character varying value that stores the category name or ID. This column is critical for incident analysis and risk management.

The site_location column represents the location where each incident occurred in the incidents table. It is a character varying value that stores the site name or ID. This column is essential for tracking incident frequency and identifying trends.

The severity column represents the level of severity for each incident recorded in the incidents table. It is a character varying value that stores the severity level (e.g., 'low', 'medium', 'high'). This column is critical for incident analysis and risk management.

The description column stores a brief description of each incident recorded in the incidents table. It is a text value that provides context for incident records and enables tracking of incident data. This column is essential for incident analysis and risk management.

columns.description: The reported_by column represents the individual who reported each incident in the incidents table. It is an integer value that stores the ID of the reporter. This column is critical for tracking incident reporting and identifying areas for improvement in incident management.

tables.description: The risk_register table stores information about potential hazards and risks, including the assessment date, hazard type, hazard description, and risk rating. This table is used to identify and prioritize risks, develop mitigation strategies, and ensure compliance with regulatory requirements.

columns.description: The risk_id column represents a unique identifier for each risk recorded in the risk_register table. It is an integer value that is used to link risks to their records and track risk data. This column is essential for risk management and compliance.

The assessment_date column represents the date on which each risk was assessed in the risk_register table. It is a date value that enables tracking of risk frequency and identifies trends. This column is critical for risk management and compliance.

The hazard_type column represents the type of hazard associated with each risk recorded in the risk_register table. It is a character varying value that stores the hazard type name or ID. This column is essential for risk management and compliance.

The hazard_description column stores a brief description of each hazard associated with each risk recorded in the risk_register table. It is a text value that provides context for risk records and enables tracking of risk data. This column is critical for risk management and compliance.

columns.description: The risk_rating column represents the level of risk associated with each risk recorded in the risk_register table. It is an integer value that stores the risk rating (e.g., 'low', 'medium', 'high'). This column is essential for risk management and compliance.

tables.description: The trainings table represents a record of employee training activities, including the training ID, employee ID, training title, completion date, and status. This table is used to track employee training records, identify training gaps, and ensure compliance with regulatory requirements.

columns.description: The training_id column represents a unique identifier for each training activity recorded in the trainings table. It is an integer value that is used to link trainings to their records and track training data. This column is critical for employee development and compliance.

The employee_id column represents the unique identifier for the employee who participated in each training activity recorded in the trainings table. It is an integer value that links trainings to employees and enables tracking of training records. This column is essential for employee development and compliance.

The training_title column stores the title of each training activity recorded in the trainings table. It is a character varying value that provides context for training records and enables tracking of training data. This column is critical for employee development and compliance.

The completion_date column represents the date on which each training activity was completed in the trainings table. It is a date value that enables tracking of training frequency and identifies trends. This column is essential for employee development and compliance.

The status column represents the current status of each training activity recorded in the trainings table. It is a character varying value that stores the status (e.g., 'in progress', 'completed', 'deferred'). This column is critical for tracking training completion and identifying areas for improvement in employee development.
